NAME
       ballerina test - execute Ballerina tests

SYNOPSIS
       ballerina test [--offline]
           [--sourceroot <path>]
           [--experimental] [--skip-lock]
           [--config <config_file>]
           [<module-name> | -a | --all]


DESCRIPTION
       Compile and run Ballerina
       test sources and print a summary of test results. You can
       execute tests in a module, or an entire Ballerina project.
    
        Use 'ballerina test <module-name>' to execute tests in the
       specified module, or '-a' or '-all' to execute tests in all modules.


OPTIONS
       --offline
           When building a module, the remote repository (Ballerina Central) is
           always checked for latest artifacts of the dependencies. If the
           '--offline' option is specified, this remote check is not done and
           the local artifacts will be used instead.

       --sourceroot <path>
            Location of the remote project root with source files. All
            executions will be relative to the path provided for
            sourceroot.

       --config <config_file>
            Provides the path to a Ballerina configuration file.
            The configuration file format is a subset of the TOML file
            format. It supports key/value pairs, tables, comments, and
            string, int, float and boolean value types.

       --skip-lock
            Build/Compile offline without downloading dependencies.

       --experimental
            Enable experimental language features.


EXAMPLES
        Run all tests in the current project
        $ ballerina test --all

        Run tests in math module
        $ ballerina test math
